@node Requirements "Requirements"

    Requirements ---------------------------------------------------------

    To use @{b}ZipTool@{ub} you need

        À an Amiga computer with OS 2.0 or higher and an SCSI interface
        À an Iomega Zip drive (SCSI version)

@endnode

@node Installation "Installation"

    Installation ---------------------------------------------------------

    Just copy @{b}ZipTool@{ub} into your C: drawer.

@endnode

@node Usage "Using ZipTool"

    Usage ----------------------------------------------------------------

    ZipTool DEVICE/A,INFO/S,WLOCK/S,RWLOCK/S,UNLOCK/S,TUNLOCK/S,
            PASSWORD/K,EJECT/S


    @{b}DEVICE@{ub}      The device name of your Zip drive. (e.g. "Zip:")

    @{b}INFO@{ub}        Print information about the current state of the Zip disk.
                This will be one of the following:

                    À Unprotected.
                    À Temporary unprotected.
                    À Write protected.
                    À Write protected with password.
                    À Read/Write protected.

    @{b}WLOCK@{ub}       Write  protect  the  current  Zip  disk.  If  PASSWORD  is
                specified,  then  the  disk  will  be  protected using the
                password.

    @{b}RWLOCK@{ub}      Read- and write protect the current Zip disk. This  option
                requires the PASSWORD option.

    @{b}UNLOCK@{ub}      Unlock the current Zip disk.

    @{b}TUNLOCK@{ub}     Temporary unlock the current Zip disk. It is only unlocked
                for  the  current  session.  Ejecting- and re-inserting it
                will lock it again.

    @{b}PASSWORD@{ub}    The password to lock or unlock the Zip disk.

    @{b}EJECT@{ub}       The disk in the Zip drive is ejected.

@endnode

